<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-14T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="481" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163Am3/413: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-15T12:00:00+09:00">October 15,
                                        1939—noon.</date><lb/>[Received October 16—6
                                    a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>522. Department’s 229, October 12, 5 p.m., to Peiping—Sisters of
                                Providence. We made formal representations to the Foreign Office on
                                October 10. Circumstances of this case were set forth as fully as
                                possible; reference was made to effort to impair American rights to
                                carry on educational work; request was made for immediate
                                termination [of] interference and for investigation.</p>
                            <p>Peiping please repeat to Chungking and Hankow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>